import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()
    ax2 = ax1.twinx()

    sns.countplot(x='source', data=data, ax=ax1, color='blue', label='Source')
    sns.countplot(x='target', data=data, ax=ax2, color='green', label='Target')

    ax1.set_ylabel('Source Count', color='blue')
    ax2.set_ylabel('Target Count', color='green')

    ax1.tick_params(axis='y', colors='blue')
    ax2.tick_params(axis='y', colors='green')

    plt.title('What is the distribution of source and target in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    source_target_counts = data.groupby(['source', 'target']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    source_target_pivot = source_target_counts.pivot('source', 'target', 'count')
    
    ax = sns.heatmap(source_target_pivot, cmap='coolwarm', annot=True, fmt='d')
    plt.title('What is the most common source and target combination in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Target')
    plt.ylabel('Source')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('source').count().reset_index()
    data_grouped.columns = ['source', 'average_targets']
    data_grouped['average_targets'] = data_grouped['average_targets'] / len(data['source'].unique())

    ax = sns.barplot(x='source', y='average_targets', data=data_grouped)
    plt.title('What is the average number of targets per source in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Source')
    plt.ylabel('Average Number of Targets')
    plt.legend(title='Sources', loc='upper right', labels=data_grouped['source'].unique())

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    unique_sources = data['source'].value_counts()
    unique_targets = data['target'].value_counts()
    combined_data = pd.concat([unique_sources, unique_targets], axis=1).fillna(0)
    combined_data.columns = ['source', 'target']
    
    ax = combined_data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of unique sources and targets in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Categories")
    plt.ylabel("Count")
    plt.legend(title="Type")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
